Adjust the relative scales in the dataset by applyig mathematical function log

The logarithm is not defined at negative values as well as 0 values.

In [19]:
# Remove negative values
my_data.loc[my_data.cons_12m < 0,"cons_12m"] = np.nan
my_data.loc[my_data.cons_gas_12m < 0,"cons_gas_12m"] = np.nan
my_data.loc[my_data.cons_last_month < 0,"cons_last_month"] = np.nan
my_data.loc[my_data.forecast_cons_12m < 0,"forecast_cons_12m"] = np.nan
my_data.loc[my_data.forecast_meter_rent_12m < 0,"forecast_meter_rent_12m"] = np.nan
my_data.loc[my_data.imp_cons < 0,"imp_cons"] = np.nan
my_data.loc[my_data.margin_gross_pow_ele < 0, "margin_gross_pow_ele"] = np.nan

Apply log transformations

In [20]:

my_data['cons_last_month'] = np.log(my_data['cons_last_month']+1)
my_data['forecast_cons_12m'] = np.log(my_data['forecast_cons_12m']+1)
my_data['forecast_meter_rent_12m'] = np.log(my_data['forecast_meter_rent_12m']+1)
my_data['imp_cons'] = np.log(my_data['imp_cons']+1)
